    "introduction": "Craig Porritt made his acting debut in 2005 in the short film '7623'. Since then he has appeared in over 40 film and television productions. Craig took his early training with Theresa Sears and David Switzer, and continued with advanced training at Walter Alza Acting Studio.During his 17 year acting career, Craig has worked with a diverse group of talented professionals, from Director Guillermo del Toro to comedian Russell Peters (as part of an ensemble cast). He has appeared in productions starring Trish Stratus, Pamela Anderson, Zoe Kravitz, Vivica A. Fox, and David Bradley.On television you may have seen Craig in The Strain, Rookie Blue, Forensic Factor, and Outlaw Bikers. His most recent credits include the film White Night, which premiered in 2020 on Prime Video, the film Peppergrass (April 2021), and the TV movie Let's Get Merried! (December 2021).",
